            <h1>User Registration</h1>
            <p>User Registration in Gadget server can be done in several ways. The user is given an option to
                create new user accounts, use their OpenID or Infocard accounts to register with the system.
            </p>
            <a name="unpw" />
            <h2>Username / Password based</h2>
            <p>The traditional way in registering with the system. the users can easily create a new account with the
                system
                and sign in.
                <br />
                <br />
                <img alt="register" src="images/reg-1.png" />
                <br />
                <br />
                <img alt="register" src="images/reg-2.png" />
                <br />
                <br />
                <img alt="register" src="images/reg-3.png" />
            </p>
            <a name="openid" />
            <h2>OpenID Based</h2>
            <p>WSO2 Gadget server also provides OpenID as an authentication mechanism. Users can register to the system
                using their OpenID
                accounts. Users with OpenIDs will be mapped with user accounts in the gadget server at the first
                login attempt. From then on the user can use OpenID for authentication.
                <br />
                <br />
                <img alt="register" src="images/reg-1.png" />
                <br />
                <br />
                <img alt="register" src="images/oid-reg-1.png" />
                <br />
                <br />
                <img alt="register" src="images/oid-reg-2.png" />
                <br />
                <br />
                <img alt="register" src="images/reg-3.png" />
            </p>
